t-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Introduction<\/h2>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7f16006 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"7f16006\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Salesforce Marketing Cloud (SFMC) is a powerful platform for businesses. It helps with email, SMS, and social media marketing. But it comes at a cost. Many companies overspend on unused features or inefficient campaigns.<\/p><p>According to research, businesses that <a href=\"https:\/\/mountainise.com\/salesforce\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">optimize Salesforce<\/a> save up to 30% on costs. With smart strategies, you can cut expenses without losing performance.<\/p><p>This guide will show you how. You\u2019ll learn to audit your usage, clean up data, and use automation effectively. Small changes can lead to big savings. Let\u2019s dive into the best ways to reduce costs while making the most of SFMC.<\/p><p><strong>Key Takeaways<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Audit your SFMC usage to cut unnecessary costs.<\/li><li>Clean and organize your data to save on storage.<\/li><li>Use automation to save time and money.<\/li><li>Train your team to use SFMC efficiently.<\/li><li>Regularly monitor and adjust your strategy.<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-f69a7fe all-sections-heading elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"f69a7fe\" data-element_type=\"widget\" id=\"section-2\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Understanding Salesforce Marketing Cloud Costs<\/h2>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4176004 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"4176004\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mountainise.com\/salesforce-marketing-cloud\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Salesforce Marketing Cloud<\/a> pricing depends on how much you use it. The cost is affected by factors like the number of contacts, emails sent, and which features you choose. For example, sending thousands of emails each month can quickly add up.<\/p><p>Additional costs may come from extra storage, premium features, or automation tools. Many businesses find themselves paying for features they don&#8217;t need or use often. This can lead to unnecessary expenses.<\/p><p>Understanding these costs is key to managing your budget. The goal is to get the most value from the tools you need while cutting back on anything extra. With the right strategy, you can keep your costs down while still running effective marketing campaigns<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4961db4 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"4961db4\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/mountainise.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/elementor\/thumbs\/Salesforce-Marketing-Cloud-pricing-depends-on-how-much-you-use-it-r10vp76zwmsldaovgplt6sqdcljcn0jg1jbq43jyuo.jpg\" title=\"Salesforce Marketing Cloud pricing depends on how much you use it\" alt=\"Salesforce Marketing Cloud pricing depends on how much you use it\" loading=\"lazy\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7a39f2c all-sections-heading elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"7a39f2c\" data-element_type=\"widget\" id=\"section-3\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Salesforce Marketing Cloud Cost Optimization Strategies<\/h2>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-297f25a elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"297f25a\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>To get the most out of Salesforce Marketing Cloud without breaking the bank, you need a clear strategy. Here are some simple ways to optimize your costs:<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-11e1b72 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"11e1b72\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Audit and Optimize Your Current Usage<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ae22c1e elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"ae22c1e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Start by taking a close look at how you&#8217;re using Salesforce Marketing Cloud. Are you paying for features you don\u2019t actually need? Many businesses use only a small portion of what Salesforce offers.<\/p><p>Begin by identifying which tools and features you\u2019re not using. If you\u2019re not taking advantage of certain add-ons or functionalities, consider removing them or downgrading your plan.<\/p><p>Focusing on the tools that align with your goals can save you a lot of money. You don\u2019t need to pay for everything available, just what helps you achieve your objectives.<\/p><p>Regularly auditing your usage helps you stay on top of what you\u2019re paying for. It\u2019s an easy way to cut costs without losing value from the platform.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-bb2701e elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"bb2701e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Optimize Data Storage and Usage<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6d17c9f elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"6d17c9f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>After you\u2019ve audited your usage and identified areas to cut back, it\u2019s time to look at your data. SMC charges based on the amount of data you store, so managing this can lead to significant savings.<\/p><p>Start by cleaning up your contact lists. Remove outdated or inactive contacts that aren\u2019t engaging with your content. This can help reduce unnecessary storage costs.<\/p><p>Also, use data extensions wisely. Only store the data that\u2019s essential for your campaigns. Segment your audience to make your communications more targeted. The more relevant your content, the better the results, and the less you\u2019ll need to store.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-835e62e elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"835e62e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Improve Email and SMS Sending Practices<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7c08d1d elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"7c08d1d\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>How do you send your emails and SMS messages in the salesforce marketing cloud? Are you focusing on quality or just sending as many as possible? The number of messages you send can really impact your costs.<\/p><p>Instead of blasting out emails and texts to everyone on your list, try to send fewer but more personalized messages. Focus on reaching the right people with content that speaks to them.<\/p><p>Use dynamic content to create messages for different groups. This can increase engagement without needing to send extra messages.<\/p><p>Also, pay attention to how often you\u2019re sending. Bombarding your audience with too many messages can lead to unsubscribes and higher costs. Keep your communication steady but not overwhelming.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2048390 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"2048390\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/mountainise.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/elementor\/thumbs\/How-do-you-send-your-emails-and-SMS-messages-in-the-salesforce-marketing-cloud-r10vxakyr9vhcexm77k5nr79i1n4x6o8hlk8vvjx9s.jpg\" title=\"How do you send your emails and SMS messages in the salesforce marketing cloud\" alt=\"How do you send your emails and SMS messages in the salesforce marketing cloud\" loading=\"lazy\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0743d72 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"0743d72\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Leverage Automation to Save Time and Money<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-3648180 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"3648180\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Automation is one of the smartest ways to save time and money with Salesforce. Instead of manually handling every step of your campaigns, you can set up automated processes that run on their own. This not only frees up time but also reduces errors and improves efficiency.<\/p><p><strong>Here\u2019s how you can use automation:<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Use <a href=\"https:\/\/www.salesforce.com\/in\/blog\/what-is-salesforce-journey-builder\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Journey Builder<\/a> to automate customer journeys. Set it up once, and let it run while you focus on other tasks.<\/li><li>Set up triggered emails based on user actions. For example, send a welcome email as soon as someone subscribes.<\/li><li>Use predictive analytics to optimize your send times. This ensures your messages hit inboxes at the perfect moment, increasing engagement.<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-fdb2bf7 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"fdb2bf7\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Negotiate with Salesforce for Better Pricing<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-56b57f1 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"56b57f1\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Did you review your Salesforce plan lately? What did you find? Are you paying for features you don\u2019t need? Or maybe you\u2019re not using all the tools you\u2019re being charged for? If that\u2019s the case, it\u2019s time to negotiate with Salesforce Services.<\/p><p>Many businesses overlook the possibility of negotiating their pricing. But Salesforce is open to adjusting contracts, especially when it\u2019s time for a renewal.<\/p><p><strong>Here\u2019s how you can do it:<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><strong>Review your current plan:<\/strong> One of the key Salesforce pricing tips for businesses is to review your plan regularly and adjust it. Look closely at what you&#8217;re paying for versus what you\u2019re actually using.<\/li><li><strong>Ask about discounts or promotions:<\/strong> Salesforce often has deals available, particularly during contract renewals.<\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/help.salesforce.com\/s\/articleView?id=ind.product_catalog_create_bundled_products.htm&amp;language=en_US&amp;type=5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Consider bundling services:<\/strong><\/a> If you use other Salesforce products, ask for a discount by combining them into one package.<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a355807 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"a355807\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Train Your Team to Maximize Efficiency<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0b60a64 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"0b60a64\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Like I always say, your system is only as good as the people using it. If your team isn\u2019t fully trained, you might be missing out on features that could save you time and money.<\/p><p>Investing in training ensures your team knows how to make the most of the platform.<\/p><p><strong>Here\u2019s how you can maximize efficiency:<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><strong>Provide regular training:<\/strong> Whether it\u2019s through Salesforce\u2019s free resources or paid programs, make sure your team is up to speed.<\/li><li><strong>Encourage certification:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.forbes.com\/councils\/forbeshumanresourcescouncil\/2024\/06\/25\/the-power-of-having-certified-it-professionals-in-your-organization\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Certified users are more productive<\/a>. Salesforce reports that certified users can be 25% more productive than those without.<\/li><li><strong>Share best practices:<\/strong> Set aside time for your team to discuss strategies and tips for using SFMC more effectively.<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-9496a9d elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"9496a9d\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/mountainise.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/elementor\/thumbs\/Train-Your-Team-to-Maximize-Efficiency-by-using-salesforce-marketing-cloud-r10wuqo7y1nsgwclw618vtcqgmsbtgge3598nbylv4.jpg\" title=\"Train Your Team to Maximize Efficiency by using salesforce marketing cloud\" alt=\"Train Your Team to Maximize Efficiency by using salesforce marketing cloud\" loading=\"lazy\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6a5cdd0 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"6a5cdd0\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Monitor and Adjust Regularly<\/h4>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a6877d7 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"a6877d7\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>After you\u2019ve made all the changes, audited your usage, cleaned up your data, and trained your team, it\u2019s important to keep an eye on how things are going.<\/p><p>Regular monitoring helps you stay on track and ensures you\u2019re not missing opportunities.<\/p><p><strong>Here\u2019s what you should do:<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><strong>Use Salesforce\u2019s reporting tools:<\/strong> Track your campaign performance and see where you\u2019re succeeding and where you could improve.<\/li><li><strong>A\/B test your campaigns:<\/strong> Try different approaches to find the most cost-effective strategies.<\/li><li><strong>Adjust based on data:<\/strong> If something isn\u2019t working, don\u2019t be afraid to change your approach.<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a6917e8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"a6917e8\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Explore Third-Party Integrations<\/h4>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-cfd402d elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"cfd402d\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Sometimes, using third-party tools alongside Salesforce can save you money while boosting your marketing efforts. Instead of paying for every feature within Salesforce, consider integrating other platforms that offer similar or complementary services at a lower cost. This approach is an effective way of saving money on Salesforce tools without compromising on performance.<\/p><p>For example, if you need extra analytics or design capabilities, tools like Mailchimp or HubSpot can be a great addition. They can work alongside Salesforce to provide value without duplicating features.<\/p><p>But it\u2019s important to review these integrations. Not all third-party tools are worth the investment. Evaluate their ROI to make sure they\u2019re providing real value.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-3588a5b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"3588a5b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Want to elevate your marketing performance? Learn how AI-powered solutions are transforming Salesforce Marketing Cloud in <a class=\"in-cell-link\" href=\"https:\/\/mountainise.com\/blog\/ai-salesforce-marketing-cloud\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">How AI is Shaping the Future of Customer Engagement<\/a>.<\/strong><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-82d6a69 all-sections-heading elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"82d6a69\" data-element_type=\"widget\" id=\"section-4\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Conclusion<\/h2>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4af7b1c elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"4af7b1c\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Reducing costs in Salesforce Marketing Cloud is possible. Start by auditing your usage. Clean your data and improve your sending practices. Use automation to save time. Negotiate with Salesforce for better pricing. Train your team and monitor your campaigns regularly.<\/p><p>Small changes can lead to big savings. Follow these tips so you can reduce marketing cloud expenses and get the most out of SFMC.<\/p><p>If you need help optimizing your Salesforce Marketing Cloud costs, <a href=\"https:\/\/mountainise.com\/contact-us\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">contact us<\/a>. We\u2019re here to guide you through the process and ensure you get the best value.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-b772fd3\" data-id=\"b772fd3\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-inner-section elementor-element elementor-element-9816b84 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"9816b84\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;sticky&quot;:&quot;top&quot;,&quot;sticky_on&quot;:[&quot;desktop&quot;],&quot;sticky_parent&quot;:&quot;yes&quot;,&quot;ekit_has_onepagescroll_dot&quot;:&quot;yes&quot;,&quot;sticky_offset&quot;:0,&quot;sticky_effects_offset&quot;:0,&quot;sticky_anchor_link_offset&quot;:0}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-no\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-inner-column elementor-element elementor-element-fba9f9a\" data-id=\"fba9f9a\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-760b142 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"760b142\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Latest WhitePaper<\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-19ee952 elementor-grid-1 elementor-grid-tablet-2 elementor-grid-mobile-1 elementor-posts--thumbnail-top elementor-posts__hover-gradient elementor-widget elementor-widget-posts\" data-id=\"19ee952\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;cards_columns&quot;:&quot;1&quot;,&quot;cards_row_gap&quot;:{&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:5,&quot;sizes&quot;:[]},&quot;cards_columns_tablet&quot;:&quot;2&quot;,&quot;cards_columns_mobile&quot;:&quot;1&quot;,&quot;cards_row_gap_tablet&quot;:{&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;sizes&quot;:[]},&quot;cards_row_gap_mobile&quot;:{&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;sizes&quot;:[]},&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"posts.cards\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-posts-container elementor-posts elementor-posts--skin-cards elementor-grid\" role=\"list\">\n\t\t\t\t<article class=\"elementor-post elementor-grid-item post-22071 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-white-papers\" role=\"listitem\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-post__card\">\n\t\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-post__thumbnail__link\" href=\"https:\/\/mountainise.com\/white-papers\/ai-powered-operations-organizational-growth\/\" tabindex=\"-1\" ><div class=\"elementor-post__thumbnail\"><img alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1088\" src=\"https:\/\/mountainise.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/Frame-42-1.png\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-image-22074\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mountainise.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\